<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="343">Note:</emphasis>
There are two Clayton sheets extant, &quot;Clayton 159&quot; and &quot;Clayton 159/451&quot; (both BM). The type designation does not distinguish between these sheets, but as they appear to be part of a single gathering, Art. 9.15 applies and the typification is effective. At some point, it may be desirable to restrict this choice to one or other sheet.
